faa-sem pack — content licence
===============================

This pack is derived from:
    Systems Engineering Manual (SEM)
    US Federal Aviation Administration (FAA)
    Version 1.0.1 (2014-06-19)

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work, 17 U.S.C. 105).
(tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

This source is a work of the United States Government, prepared by the US Federal
Aviation Administration, and is therefore NOT subject to copyright protection in
the United States (17 U.S.C. 105). It is in the public domain: anyone may
reproduce, transform, and redistribute it for any purpose, including commercially,
without permission and without any attribution or share-alike obligation.

Attribution to the US Federal Aviation Administration is provided as a courtesy
(see the repository NOTICE), not a legal obligation. The FAA does not endorse this
pack or its authors.

Caveat carried forward from the source: the FAA Systems Engineering Manual is
guidance, not policy (binding acquisition policy lives in the FAA Acquisition
Management System, via FAST), and it is a pointer document — it defers detailed
methodology to companion references (FAA-HDBK-006A for RMA, the FAA Safety
Management System Manual for system safety, and the NIST 800-series for
information security). This pack is a synthesized, transformed set of reference
notes; it reproduces no long verbatim passages of the source.

